Ultrasonic Sensor Pins (HC-SR04)

The ultrasonic sensor has 4 pins:

1	VCC	Power  ->    supply (5V),
2	TRIG	  ->     Trigger input,
3	ECHO	  ->     Echo output,
4	GND        -> 	Ground,
2. Arduino Connection.
 Basic Wiring;
Ultrasonic Sensor	Arduino
VCC	                  5V
GND	                  GND
TRIG	            Digital Pin (e.g., D9)
ECHO	            Digital Pin (e.g., D10)
3. How Each Pin Works
VCC & GND->Provide power to the sensor
VCC → 5V
GND → Ground
TRIG (Trigger Pin):->
This is an input pin
Arduino sends a HIGH pulse (10 microseconds)

This tells the sensor:
“Start measuring distance”

ECHO (Echo Pin):
This is an output pin
Sensor sends a pulse back to Arduino

Pulse duration = time taken for sound to travel to object and return

4. Working Principle:

The sensor uses sound waves based on the concept of:

Ultrasonic Distance Measurement

Steps:

TRIG sends signal
Sensor emits ultrasonic wave
Wave hits object and reflects
ECHO pin goes HIGH
Time is measured
5. Distance Formula:

Distance is calculated using:
Distance=Time×Speed of Sound/2
	​
Speed of sound ≈ 343 m/s

